VALUES
(42, 13, 21, 43, 15, 2, 2, 'the whole was leavened', 'Growth and Transformation', 'This connection highlights the theme of growth and transformation in both passages. The leaven in Luke symbolizes how small actions can lead to significant change, while John emphasizes the process of purging to enhance fruitfulness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 21, 50, 1, 6, 6, 'the whole was leavened', 'Transformation and Growth', 'This connection highlights the theme of gradual transformation. In Luke, the leaven symbolizes the pervasive influence of the Kingdom of God, while Philippians emphasizes the ongoing work God performs in believers until completion.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 21, 59, 1, 21, 21, 'the whole was leavened', 'Transformation Through the Word', 'This connection highlights the transformative power of both leaven and the engrafted word. Just as leaven permeates and changes the meal, the word is able to save and transform the soul.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 22, 42, 9, 51, 51, 'journeying toward Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the journey toward Jerusalem, highlighting a significant focus in Jesus'' ministry. The steadfastness in going to Jerusalem in Luke 9:51 connects with the teaching and journeying in Luke 13:22.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 22, 40, 9, 35, 35, 'cities and villages', 'Jesus'' Ministry in Cities', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' movement through cities and villages while teaching. They highlight his role as a teacher and healer among the people.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 22, 41, 10, 32, 34, 'journeying toward Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the journey toward Jerusalem, highlighting Jesus'' movement and purpose. Luke notes Jesus teaching as he travels, while Mark details the impending events that will occur there.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 22, 42, 4, 43, 44, 'journeying toward Jerusalem', 'Preaching Mission of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' commitment to preaching in various locations. In Luke 13:22, he is described as journeying through cities and villages, while in Luke 4:43-44, he expresses the necessity to preach in other cities as part of his mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 22, 44, 10, 38, 38, NULL, 'Jesus'' Ministry of Goodness', 'This connection highlights the active ministry of Jesus as he ''went about doing good'' in both passages. Luke emphasizes his journey through cities and villages, while Acts describes his actions of healing and helping those oppressed.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 22, 41, 6, 6, 6, NULL, 'Teaching in Villages', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' activity of teaching in villages. This connection highlights his itinerant ministry as he moves through various locations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 23, 40, 7, 14, 14, 'few that be saved', 'Salvation and the Narrow Path', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation being limited. Both passages emphasize that few will find the path that leads to life.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 23, 40, 22, 14, 14, 'be saved', 'Salvation and Divine Selection', 'This connection highlights the theme of exclusivity in salvation. Both passages emphasize that while many may be called or seek salvation, only a few are ultimately chosen or saved.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 23, 42, 12, 13, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Salvation and Covetousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of what constitutes true value in life. In both passages, Jesus addresses the misconceptions about salvation and material wealth, emphasizing that life is not defined by possessions.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 23, 43, 21, 21, 22, 'Lord, are there few that be saved?', 'Salvation and Following Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of discipleship and the question of salvation. Both passages emphasize the importance of individual focus on following Jesus amidst concerns about others'' fates.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 23, 41, 13, 4, 5, 'are there few that be saved', 'Salvation and Deception Themes', 'This connection highlights the concern for salvation and the potential for deception. Both passages emphasize the need for vigilance in the face of questions about salvation and the signs of the end times.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 23, 42, 21, 7, 8, 'be saved', 'Salvation and Deception Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of discernment regarding salvation and false claims. The question of who will be saved in Luke 13:23 connects to the warning against deception in Luke 21:7-8, highlighting the need for vigilance in faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 23, 44, 1, 7, 8, NULL, 'Salvation and Witnessing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation and the call to witness. In Luke, the question of who will be saved is posed, while in Acts, the emphasis is on being witnesses to spread the message of salvation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 24, 40, 7, 13, 14, 'strait gate', 'Strait Gate and Narrow Way', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of entering through a ''strait gate'' and the difficulty of finding the path to life. They highlight the contrast between the narrow way that leads to life and the broad way that leads to destruction.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 24, 61, 1, 10, 10, 'Strive to enter in at the strait gate', 'Diligence in Spiritual Pursuit', 'This connection highlights the theme of striving and diligence in spiritual matters. Both passages emphasize the necessity of effort to secure one''s place in the faith.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 24, 46, 9, 24, 27, 'Strive to enter in at the strait gate', 'Striving for Spiritual Mastery', 'Both passages emphasize the need to strive and compete for spiritual goals. Luke 13:24''s call to ''strive to enter'' parallels 1 Corinthians 9:24''s exhortation to ''run, that ye may obtain,'' highlighting the effort required in the Christian faith.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 24, 58, 4, 11, 11, 'Strive to enter in at the strait gate', 'Striving for Spiritual Entry', 'Both passages emphasize the need to strive or labor to enter into a state of spiritual fulfillment or rest. They highlight the importance of effort in the pursuit of salvation and the potential consequences of unbelief.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 24, 42, 21, 36, 36, 'Strive to enter in at the strait gate', 'Striving and Worthiness Connection', 'This connection highlights the themes of striving and preparedness for entering the kingdom of God. Both passages emphasize the necessity of effort and vigilance in seeking salvation and standing before the Son of man.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 24, 26, 33, 31, 31, 'strive to enter in at the strait gate', 'Striving and Heart''s Intent', 'This connection highlights the theme of striving for true commitment versus superficial engagement. Both passages emphasize the importance of genuine action over mere words, as seen in the call to ''strive'' and the critique of those who ''show much love'' without true intent.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 24, 50, 2, 12, 13, 'Strive to enter in at the strait gate', 'Striving for Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of striving for salvation. Both passages emphasize the necessity of effort in the process of salvation, with Luke urging to ''strive to enter'' and Philippians encouraging believers to ''work out your own salvation.''', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 25, 40, 25, 10, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Closed Doors', 'Both passages emphasize the moment when the door is shut and the subsequent plea of ''Lord, Lord, open to us.'' This connection highlights the theme of exclusion and the recognition of those who are not known by the master.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 25, 42, 13, 27, 27, 'I know you not whence ye are', 'Rejection of the Unrecognized', 'Both passages emphasize the master''s declaration of not knowing the individuals seeking entry. This highlights the theme of exclusion based on recognition and the consequences of iniquity.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 25, 40, 7, 21, 23, 'I know you not', 'Connection of Rejection and Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejection by the master due to a lack of true relationship. They highlight the phrase ''I know you not'' as a critical response to those who claim to know the Lord but do not do His will.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 25, 42, 6, 46, 46, 'Lord, Lord', 'Connection of Lordship and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of calling Jesus ''Lord'' while failing to obey His commands. Both passages emphasize the importance of genuine relationship and action in faith, as mere acknowledgment is insufficient.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 25, 23, 55, 6, 6, 'Lord, Lord, open unto us', 'Seeking the Lord''s Presence', 'This connection highlights the urgency of seeking the Lord before it is too late. Both passages emphasize the importance of calling upon the Lord while He is near, contrasting with the moment when the door is shut and access is denied.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 25, 47, 6, 2, 2, 'Lord, Lord, open unto us', 'Salvation and Acceptance', 'Both passages emphasize the urgency of seeking salvation. Luke highlights the moment when the door is shut, while 2 Corinthians stresses that now is the accepted time for salvation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 13, 25, 19, 32, 6, 6, 'Lord, Lord, open unto us', 'Prayer and Divine Response', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of seeking the Lord while He may be found. The urgency in Luke''s warning about the closed door parallels the call in Psalms for the godly to pray in times of need.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
